' Markdown: inline formatting, headings, lists, toggling, mixed content
#md on
' Inline formatting
"**Bold text**"
"*Italic text*"
"***Bold and italic***"
"++Underlined text++"
"~~Strikethrough text~~"
"~Subscript~"
"^Superscript^"
' Combined inline
"**Bold** and *italic* and ++underline++ together"
"H~2~O is water, E = mc^2^"
' Headings
"### Heading 3"
"#### Heading 4"
"##### Heading 5"
"###### Heading 6"
"### **Bold Heading**"
' Horizontal rule
"---"
' Lists
"- Item 1"
"- Item 2"
"- Item 3"
"1. First"
"2. Second"
"3. Third"
' Markdown with expressions
a = 42
b = 3.14
c = a + b
"The value of **a** is "a
"The sum **a + b** = "c
' Markdown in single-quote comments
'**Bold in single quotes**'
'Value = 'a' (computed)'
' Mixed markdown and HTML
"**Bold markdown** with <span style='color:red'>red HTML</span>"
' Markdown in macros
#def mdNote$(text$) = '**Note:** 'text$
#def mdSub$(label$; sub$) = label$'~'sub$'~'
mdNote$('This is important')
mdSub$('x'; 'i')
' Markdown toggling
#md off
"**Not parsed as markdown**"
#md on
"**Parsed as markdown again**"
' Markdown in control flow
x = 100
#if x > 50
	"**x exceeds 50**"
#else
	"*x is within limits*"
#end if
#md off
